column9: Plural of (H1116) bamah; heights; or (fully) Bamowth Bahal {baw-moth' bah'-al}; from the same and (H1168) Ba'al; heights of Baal; Bamoth or Bamoth-Baal, a place East of the Jordan -- Bamoth, Bamoth-baal. see HEBREW (H1116) bamah see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al

column8: afflicted, age, anointed one, appointed to, arrow
column9: From (H1129) banah; a son (as a builder of the family name), in the widest sense (of literal and figurative relationship, including grandson, subject, nation, quality or condition, etc., (like (H1) 'ab, (H251) 'ach, etc.)) -- + afflicted, age, (Ahoh-) (Ammon-) (Hachmon-) (Lev-)ite, (anoint-)ed one, appointed to, (+) arrow, (Assyr-) (Babylon-) (Egypt-) (Grec-)ian, one born, bough, branch, breed, + (young) bullock, + (young) calf, X came up in, child, colt, X common, X corn, daughter, X of first, + firstborn, foal, + very fruitful, + postage, X in, + kid, + lamb, (+) man, meet, + mighty, + nephew, old, (+) people, + rebel, + robber, X servant born, X soldier, son, + spark, + steward, + stranger, X surely, them of, + tumultuous one, + valiant(-est), whelp, worthy, young (one), youth. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H1) 'ab see HEBREW (H251) 'ach
The same as (H1121) ben; Ben, an Israelite -- Ben. see HEBREW (H1121) ben
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1121) ben -- child, son, young. see HEBREW (H1121) ben
(Aramaic) or bnah (Aramaic) {ben-aw'}; corresponding to (H1129) banah; to build -- build, make. see HEBREW (H1129) banah

column7: son of Abinadab, one of Solomon\'s leaders
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H40) 'Abiymelek; (the) son of Abinadab; Ben-Abinadab, an Israelite -- the son of Abinadab. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H40) 'Abiymelek

column7: son of my sorrow, Rachel\'s name for Benjamin
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H205) 'aven; son of my sorrow; Ben-Oni, the original name of Benjamin -- Ben-oni. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H205) 'aven

column7: son of a man, one of Solomon\'s leaders
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H1397) geber; son of (the) hero; Ben- Geber, an Israelite -- the son of Geber. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H1397) geber

column7: son of Deker, one of Solomon\'s leaders
column9: From (H1121) ben and a derivative of (H1856) daqar; son of piercing (or of a lance); Ben-Deker, an Israelite -- the son of Dekar. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H1856) daqar

column8: begin to builder, obtain children, make, repair, set up, surely
column9: A primitive root; to build (literally and figuratively) -- (begin to) build(-er), obtain children, make, repair, set (up), X surely.

column7: son of Hadad, the name of several Aramean (Syrian) kings
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H1908) Hadad; son of Hadad; Ben-Hadad, the name of several Syrian kings -- Ben-hadad. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H1908) Hadad
From (H1129) banah; built up; Binnui, an Israelite -- Binnui. see HEBREW (H1129) banah

column7: son of Zoheth, a man of Judah
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2105) Zowcheth; son of Zocheth; Ben- Zocheth, an Israelite -- Ben-zoketh. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2105) Zowcheth

column7: son of Hur, one of Solomon\'s leaders
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2354) Chuwr; son of Chur; Ben-Chur, an Israelite -- the son of Hur. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2354) Chuwr

column7: son of might, one of Jehoshaphat\'s leaders
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2428) chayil; son of might; Ben-Chail, an Israelite -- Ben-hail. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2428) chayil

column7: son of Hanan, a man of Judah
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2605) Chanan; son of Chanan; Ben- Chanan, an Israelite -- Ben-hanan. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2605) Chanan

column7: son of mercy, one of Solomon\'s leaders
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2617) checed; son of kindness; Ben- Chesed, an Israelite -- the son of Hesed. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2617) checed
From (H1129) banah; built; Bani, the name of five Israelites -- Bani. see HEBREW (H1129) banah
Or (fuller) Buwniy {boo-nee'}; from (H1129) banah; built; Bunni or Buni, an Israelite -- Bunni. see HEBREW (H1129) banah

column7: sons of lightning, a city in Dan
column9: From the plural construction of (H1121) ben and (H1300) baraq; sons of lightning, Bene-berak, a place in Palestine -- Bene-barak. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H1300) baraq
Feminine from (H1129) banah; a structure -- building. see HEBREW (H1129) banah

column7: Yah has built up, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or (prolonged) Bnayahuw {ben-aw-yaw'-hoo}; from (H1129) banah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has built; Benajah, the name of twelve Israelites -- Benaiah. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: sons of Jaakan, a place in the desert
column9: From the plural of (H1121) ben and (H3292) Ya'aqan; sons of Yaakan; Bene-Jaakan, a place in the Desert -- Bene-jaakan. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H3292) Ya'aqan
Dual of (H996) beyn; a double interval, i.e. The space between two armies -- + champion. see HEBREW (H996) beyn

column7: son of (the) right hand, youngest son of Jacob, also the name of two other Isr
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H3225) yamiyn; son of (the) right hand; Binjamin, youngest son of Jacob; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory -- Benjamin. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H3225) yamiyn

Sometimes (with the article inserted) Ben-ha-yminiy {ben-hah-yem-ee-nee'}; with (H376) 'iysh inserted (1 Sam. 9:1) Ben-miysh Ymiyniy {ben-eesh' yem-ee-nee'}; son of a man of Jemini; or shortened (1 Sam. 9:4; Esth. 2:5) eiysh Ymiyniy {eesh yem-ee-nee'}; a man of Jemini, or (1 Sam. 20:1) simply Yminiy {yem-ee-nee'}; a Jeminite; (plural Bniy Ymiyniy {ben- ay' yem-ee-nee'}; patron from (H1144) Binyamiyn; a Benjaminite, or descendent of Benjamin -- Benjamite, of Benjamin. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh see HEBREW (H1144) Binyamiyn
From (H1129) banah; an edifice -- building. see HEBREW (H1129) banah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1146) binyan -- building. see HEBREW (H1146) binyan
Probably from (H1121) ben with pron. Suff.; our son; Beninu, an Israelite -- Beninu. see HEBREW (H1121) ben
(Aramaic) of uncertain affinity; to be enraged -- be angry.
Or Bincah {bin-aw'}; of uncertain derivation; Bina or Binah, an Israelite -- Binea, Bineah.

column7: son of my people, a son of Lot
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H5971) am with pronomial suffix; son of my people; Ben-Ammi, a son of Lot -- Ben-ammi. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H5971) am
From (H5475) cowd and (H3050) Yahh with prepositional prefix; in (the) counsel of Jehovah; Besodejah, an Israelite -- Besodeiah. see HEBREW (H5475) cowd see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H947) buwc; domineering; Besai, one of the Nethinim -- Besai. see HEBREW (H947) buwc
From an unused root meaning to be sour; an immature grape -- unripe grape.
From the same as (H1154) becer -- sour grape. see HEBREW (H1154) becer

column8: ask, desire, make petition, pray, request, seek
column9: (Aramaic) or b ah (Aramaic) {beh-aw'}; corresponding to (H1158) ba'ah; to seek or ask -- ask, desire, make (petition), pray, request, seek. see HEBREW (H1158) ba'ah

column7: away from, behind, about, on behalf of
column8: about, at by means of, for, over, through, up on, within
column9: From (H5704) ad with prepositional prefix; in up to or over against; generally at, beside, among, behind, for, etc. -- about, at by (means of), for, over, through, up (-on), within. see HEBREW (H5704) ad

column7: to inquire, cause to swell or boil up
column8: cause, inquire, seek up, swell out
column9: A primitive root; to gush over, i.e. To swell; (figuratively) to desire earnestly; by implication to ask -- cause, inquire, seek up, swell out.
(Aramaic) from (H1156) b'a'; a request -- petition. see HEBREW (H1156) b'a'

column7: a burning, father of an Edomite king, also the father of Balaam
column9: From (H1197) ba'ar (in the sense of burning); a lamp; Beor, the name of the father of an Edomitish king; also of that of Balaam -- Beor. see HEBREW (H1197) ba'ar
Masculine plural from (H1204) ba'ath; alarms -- terrors. see HEBREW (H1204) ba'ath

column7: quickness, an ancestor of David, also a pillar before the temple
column9: From an unused root of uncertain meaning; Boaz, the ancestor of David; also the name of a pillar in front of the temple -- Boaz.
A primitive root; to trample down, i.e. (figuratively) despise -- kick.
From (H1158) ba'ah; a prayer -- grave. see HEBREW (H1158) ba'ah
From (H1197) ba'ar (in the sense of eating): cattle -- beast, cattle. see HEBREW (H1197) ba'ar

column8: have dominion over, be husband, married, wife
column9: A primitive root; to be master; hence, (as denominative from (H1167) ba'al) to marry -- have dominion (over), be husband, marry(-ried, X wife). see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al

column8: archer, babbler, bird, captain, chief man, confederate, have to do, dreamer,
column9: From (H1166) ba'al; a master; hence, a husband, or (figuratively) owner (often used with another noun in modifications of this latter sense) -- + archer, + babbler, + bird, captain, chief man, + confederate, + have to do, + dreamer, those to whom it is due, + furious, those that are given to it, great, + hairy, he that hath it, have, + horseman, husband, lord, man, + married, master, person, + sworn, they of. see HEBREW (H1166) ba'al
The same as (H1167) ba'al; Baal, a Phoenician deity -- Baal, (plural) Baalim. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1167) ba'al -- + chancellor. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al

column7: Baal of (the) covenant, a Shechemite god
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H1285) briyth; Baal of (the) covenant; Baal-Berith, a special deity of the Shechemites -- Baal-berith. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H1285) briyth

column7: Baal of fortune, a place near Mount Hermon
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H1409) gad; Baal of Fortune; Baal-Gad, a place in Syria -- Baal-gad. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H1409) gad
Feminine of (H1167) ba'al; a mistress -- that hath, mistress. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al

column7: the name of several places in Isr
column9: The same as (H1172) ba'alah; Baalah, the name of three places in Palestine -- Baalah. see HEBREW (H1172) ba'alah

column7: possessor of abundance, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and (H1995) hamown; possessor of a multitude; Baal-Hamon, a place in Palestine -- Baal-hamon. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H1995) hamown

column7: mistresses, a city in S. Judah, also a city of unc. location
column9: Plural of (H1172) ba'alah; mistresses; Bealoth, a place in Palestine -- Bealoth, in Aloth (by mistake for a plural from (H5927) alah with prepositional prefix). see HEBREW (H1172) ba'alah see HEBREW (H5927) alah

column7: Baal of flies, a Philistine god
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H2070) zbuwb; Baal of (the) Fly; Baal-Zebub, a special deity of the Ekronites -- Baal-zebub. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H2070) zbuwb

column7: Baal is gracious, a king of Edom, also an Israelite
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and (H2603) chanan; possessor of grace; Baal-Chanan, the name of an Edomite, also of an Israelite -- Baal-hanan. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H2603) chanan

column7: possessor of a court, a city between Ephraim and Benjamin
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and a modification of (H2691) chatser; possessor of a village; Baal-Chatsor, a place in Palestine -- Baal-hazor. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H2691) chatser

column7: Baal of Hermon, the center of Baal worship on Mount Hermon
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and (H2768) Chermown; possessor of Hermon; Baal-Chermon, a place in Palestine -- Baal-hermon. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H2768) Chermown

column7: my Baal, a symbolic name for Yah
column9: From (H1167) ba'al with pron. Suff.; my master; Baali, a symbolical name for Jehovah -- Baali. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al

From the plural of (H1168) Ba'al and the plural of (H1116) bamah; Baals of (the) heights; Baale-Bamoth, a place East of the Jordan -- lords of the high places. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H1116) bamah

column7: Baal knows, a son of David
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H3045) yada'; Baal has known; Beeljada, an Israelite -- Beeliada. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H3045) yada'

column7: Yah is lord, one of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and (H3050) Yahh; Jah (is) master; Bealjah, an Israelite -- Bealiah. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: Baal of Judah, the center of Baal worship in Judah
column9: From the plural of (H1167) ba'al and (H3063) Yhuwdah; masters of Judah; Baale-Jehudah, a place in Palestine -- Baale of Judah. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H3063) Yhuwdah

column7: perhaps "son of delight", an Ammonite king
column9: Probably from a derivative of (H5965) alac with prepositional prefix; in exultation; Baalis, an Ammonitish king -- Baalis. see HEBREW (H5965) alac

column7: Baal of (the) habitation, a place East of the Jordan
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H4583) ma'own; Baal of (the) habitation (of) (compare (H1010) Beyth Ba'al m'own); Baal-Meon, a place East of the Jordan -- Baal-meon. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H4583) ma'own see HEBREW (H1010) Beyth Ba'al m'own

column7: Baal of Peor, a Moabite god
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H6465) p'owr; Baal of Peor; Baal-Peor, a Moabitish deity -- Baal-peor. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H6465) p'owr

column7: possessor of breaches, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and the plural of (H6556) perets; possessor of breaches; Baal-Peratsim, a place in Palestine -- Baal- perazim. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H6556) perets

column7: Baal of winter, a place in Egypt
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H6828) tsaphown (in the sense of cold) (according to others an Egyptian form of Typhon, the destroyer); Baal of winter; Baal-Tsephon, a place in Eqypt -- Baal-zephon. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H6828) tsaphown

column7: Baal of Shalishah, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H1168) Ba'al and (H8031) Shalishah; Baal of Shalishah, Baal-Shalishah, a place in Palestine -- Baal-shalisha. see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H8031) Shalishah
A modification of (H1172) ba'alah; mistressship; Baalath, a place in Palestine -- Baalath. see HEBREW (H1172) ba'alah

column7: mistress of a well, a city in Simeon
column9: From (H1172) ba'alah and (H875) 'er; mistress of a well; Baalath-Beer, a place in Palestine -- Baalath-beer. see HEBREW (H1172) ba'alah see HEBREW (H875) 'er

column7: possessor of palms, a place near Gibeah
column9: From (H1167) ba'al and (H8558) tamar; possessor of (the) palm-tree; Baal-Tamar, a place in Palestine -- Baal-tamar. see HEBREW (H1167) ba'al see HEBREW (H8558) tamar

column7: a place East of the Jordan
column9: Probably a contraction of (H1010) Beyth Ba'al m'own; Beon, a place East of the Jordan -- Beon. see HEBREW (H1010) Beyth Ba'al m'own
The same as (H1196) Ba'anah; Banana, the name of four Israelite -- Baana, Baanah. see HEBREW (H1196) Ba'anah
From a derivative of (H6031) anah with prepositional prefix; in affliction -- Baanah, the name of four Israelites -- Baanah. see HEBREW (H6031) anah

column8: be brutish, bring put, take away, burn, cause to eat up, feed, heat, kindle,
column9: A primitive root; to kindle, i.e. Consume (by fire or by eating); also (as denominative from (H1198) ba'ar) to be(-come) brutish -- be brutish, bring (put, take) away, burn, (cause to) eat (up), feed, heat, kindle, set ((on fire)), waste. see HEBREW (H1198) ba'ar
From (H1197) ba'ar; properly, foot (as consumed); i.e. (by exten.) Of cattle brutishness; (concretely) stupid -- brutish (person), foolish. see HEBREW (H1197) ba'ar
From (H1198) ba'ar; brutish: Baara, an Israelitish woman -- Baara. see HEBREW (H1198) ba'ar
From (H1197) ba'ar; a burning -- fire. see HEBREW (H1197) ba'ar
From an unused root meaning to stink; offensiveness; Basha, a king of Israel -- Baasha.
From (H6213) asah and (H3050) Yahh with a prepositional prefix; in (the) work of Jah; Baasejah, an Israelite -- Baaseiah. see HEBREW (H6213) asah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: perhaps "house of Ashtoreth", a Levitical city in Manasseh
column9: From (H6251) ashtrah (as singular of (H6252) Ashtarowth) with a prepositional prefix; with Ashtoreth; Beeshterah, a place East of the Jordan -- Beeshterah. see HEBREW (H6251) ashtrah see HEBREW (H6252) Ashtarowth

column8: affright, be make afraid, terrify, trouble
column9: A primitive root; to fear -- affright, be (make) afraid, terrify, trouble.
From (H1204) ba'ath; fear -- trouble. see HEBREW (H1204) ba'ath
Probably the same as (H948) buwts; mud (as whitish clay) -- mire. see HEBREW (H948) buwts
Intensive from (H1206) bots; a swamp -- fen, mire(-ry place). see HEBREW (H1206) bots
From (H1219) batsar; inaccessible, i.e. Lofty -- vintage (by confusion with (H1210) batsiyr). see HEBREW (H1219) batsar see HEBREW (H1210) batsiyr
Perhaps the same as (H1153) Bcay; Betsai, the name of two Israelites -- Bezai. see HEBREW (H1153) Bcay
From (H1219) batsar; clipped, i.e. The grape crop -- vintage. see HEBREW (H1219) batsar
From an unused root apparently meaning to peel; an onion -- onion.

column7: in the shadow (protection) of El, two Israelites
column9: Probably from (H6738) tsel and (H410) 'el with a prepositional prefix; in (the) shadow (i.e. Protection) of God; Betsalel, the name of two Israelites -- Bezaleel. see HEBREW (H6738) tsel see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or Batsliyth {bats-leeth'}; from the same as (H1211) btsel; a peeling; Batsluth or Batslith, an Israelite -- Bazlith, Bazluth. see HEBREW (H1211) btsel

column7: to cut off, break off, gain by violence
column8: be covetous, cut off, finish, fulfill, gain greedily, be given to covetousness, greedy,
column9: A primitive root to break off, i.e. (usually) plunder; figuratively, to finish, or (intransitively) stop -- (be) covet(- ous), cut (off), finish, fulfill, gain (greedily), get, be given to (covetousness), greedy, perform, be wounded.

column7: gain made by violence, unjust gain, profit
column9: From (H1214) batsa'; plunder; by extension, gain (usually unjust) -- covetousness, (dishonest) gain, lucre, profit. see HEBREW (H1214) batsa'
A primitive root; perhaps to swell up, i.e. Blister -- swell.
From (H1216) batseq; dough (as swelling by fermentation) -- dough, flour. see HEBREW (H1216) batseq
From (H1216) batseq; a swell of ground; Botscath, a place in Palestine -- Bozcath, Boskath. see HEBREW (H1216) batseq

column7: to cut off, make inaccessible, enclose
column8: cut off, fortify, grape gatherer, mighty things, restrain, strong, wall up,
column9: A primitive root; to clip off; specifically (as denominative from (H1210) batsiyr) to gather grapes; also to be isolated (i.e. Inaccessible by height or fortification) -- cut off, (de-)fenced, fortify, (grape) gather(-er), mighty things, restrain, strong, wall (up), withhold. see HEBREW (H1210) batsiyr
From (H1219) batsar; strictly a clipping, i.e. Gold (as dug out) -- gold defence. see HEBREW (H1219) batsar

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine person
column7: fortress, a city in Reuben, also a descendant of Asher
column9: The same as (H1220) betser, an inaccessible spot; Betser, a place in Palestine; also an Israelite -- Bezer. see HEBREW (H1220) betser
Another form for (H1220) betser; gold -- gold. see HEBREW (H1220) betser
Feminine from (H1219) batsar; an enclosure, i.e. Sheep fold -- Bozrah. see HEBREW (H1219) batsar

column7: fortress, a city in Edom, also one in Moab
column9: The same as (H1223) botsrah; Botsrah, a place in Edom -- Bozrah. see HEBREW (H1223) botsrah
Masculine intensive from (H1219) batsar; a fortress -- stronghold. see HEBREW (H1219) batsar
Feminine intensive from (H1219) batsar; restraint (of rain), i.e. Drought -- dearth, drought. see HEBREW (H1219) batsar
The same as (H1228) baqbuk; Bakbuk, one of the Nethinim -- Bakbuk. see HEBREW (H1228) baqbuk
From (H1238) baqaq; a bottle (from the gurgling in emptying) -- bottle, cruse. see HEBREW (H1238) baqaq
From (H1228) baqbuk and (H3050) Yahh; emptying (i.e. Wasting) of Jah; Bakbukjah, an Israelite -- Bakbukiah. see HEBREW (H1228) baqbuk see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Reduplicated from (H1239) baqar; searcher; Bakbakkar, an Israelite -- Bakbakkar. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar
From (H1238) baqaq; wasteful; Bukki, the name of two Israelites -- Bukki. see HEBREW (H1238) baqaq
From (H1238) baqaq and (H3050) Yahh; wasting of Jah; Bukkijah, an Israelite -- Bukkiah. see HEBREW (H1238) baqaq see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H1234) baqa'; a fissure -- breach, cleft. see HEBREW (H1234) baqa'

column7: to cleave, break open or through
column8: make a breach, break forth into, out, in pieces
column9: A primitive root; to cleave; generally, to rend, break, rip or open -- make a breach, break forth (into, out, in pieces, through, up), be ready to burst, cleave (asunder), cut out, divide, hatch, rend (asunder), rip up, tear, win.
From (H1234) baqa'; a section (half) of a shekel, i.e. A beka (a weight and a coin) -- bekah, half a shekel. see HEBREW (H1234) baqa'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1237) biq'ah -- plain. see HEBREW (H1237) biq'ah
From (H1234) baqa'; properly, a split, i.e. A wide level valley between mountains -- plain, valley. see HEBREW (H1234) baqa'

column8: make empty, fail, utterly, make void
column9: A primitive root; to pour out, i.e. To empty, figuratively, to depopulate; by analogy, to spread out (as a fruitful vine) -- (make) empty (out), fail, X utterly, make void.

column8: make inquire ry, make search, seek out
column9: A primitive root; properly, to plough, or (generally) break forth, i.e. (figuratively) to inspect, admire, care for, consider -- (make) inquire (-ry), (make) search, seek out.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1239) baqar -- inquire, make search. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar

column8: bull, calf, cow, great cattle, heifer, herd,
column9: From (H1239) baqar; beef cattle or an animal of the ox family of either gender (as used for plowing); collectively, a herd -- beeve, bull (+ -ock), + calf, + cow, great (cattle), + heifer, herd, kine, ox. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar
From (H1239) baqar; properly, dawn (as the break of day); generally, morning -- (+) day, early, morning, morrow. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar
Intensive from (H1239) baqar; a looking after -- seek out. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar
From (H1239) baqar; properly, examination, i.e. (by implication) punishment -- scourged. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar

column8: ask, beg, beseech, desire, enquire, get, make inquisition, procure,
column9: A primitive root; to search out (by any method, specifically in worship or prayer); by implication, to strive after -- ask, beg, beseech, desire, enquire, get, make inquisition, procure, (make) request, require, seek (for).
From (H1245) baqash; a petition -- request. see HEBREW (H1245) baqash
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1121) ben; a son, grandson, etc. -- X old, son. see HEBREW (H1121) ben
Borrowed (as a title) from (H1247) bar; the heir (apparent to the throne) -- son. see HEBREW (H1247) bar
From (H1305) barar (in its various senses); beloved; also pure, empty -- choice, clean, clear, pure. see HEBREW (H1305) barar
Or bar {bar}; from (H1305) barar (in the sense of winnowing); grain of any kind (even while standing in the field); by extens. The open country -- corn, wheat. see HEBREW (H1305) barar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1250) bar; a field -- field. see HEBREW (H1250) bar
From (H1305) barar; purify -- cleanness, pureness. see HEBREW (H1305) barar
The same as (H1252) bor; vegetable lye (from its cleansing); used as a soap for washing, or a flux for metals -- X never so, purely. see HEBREW (H1252) bor

column8: choose, create creator, cut down, dispatch, do, make fat
column9: A primitive root; (absolutely) to create; (qualified) to cut down (a wood), select, feed (as formative processes) -- choose, create (creator), cut down, dispatch, do, make (fat).

column7: he has given a son, a Babylonian king
column9: A variation of (H4757) Mro'dak Bal'adan; Berodak-Baladan, a Babylonian king -- Berodach-baladan.Birliy. see HEBREW (H4757) Mro'dak Bal'adan
From (H1254) bara' and (H8050) Shmuw'el; Jah has created; Berajah, an Israelite -- Beraiah. see HEBREW (H1254) bara' see HEBREW (H8050) Shmuw'el
By reduplication from (H1250) bar; a fowl (as fattened on grain) -- fowl. see HEBREW (H1250) bar
A primitive root, to hail -- hail.
From (H1258) barad; hail -hail ((stones)). see HEBREW (H1258) barad

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: a place near Kadesh, also an Ephraimite
column9: From (H1258) barad; hail; Bered, the name of a place south of Palestine, also of an Israelite -- Bered. see HEBREW (H1258) barad
From (H1258) barad; spotted (as if with hail) -- grisled. see HEBREW (H1258) barad

column8: choose, cause to eat, manifest, give meat
column9: A primitive root; to select; also (as denominative from (H1250) bar) to feed; also (as equivalent to (H1305) barar) to render clear (Eccl. 3:18) -- choose, (cause to) eat, manifest, (give) meat. see HEBREW (H1250) bar see HEBREW (H1305) barar
Passive participle from (H1288) barak; blessed; Baruk, the name of three Israelites -- Baruch. see HEBREW (H1288) barak
Probably of foreign origin; damask (stuff of variegated thread) -- rich apparel.
Of uncertain derivation; a cypress (?) Tree; hence, a lance or a musical instrument (as made of that wood) -- fir (tree).
A variation of (H1265) browsh; the cypress (or some elastic tree) -- fir. see HEBREW (H1265) browsh
From (H1262) barah; food -- meat. see HEBREW (H1262) barah
Or Berothay {bay-ro-that'-ee}; probably from (H1266) browth; cypress or cypresslike; Berothah or Berothai, a place north of Palestine -- Berothah, Berothai. see HEBREW (H1266) browth
Probably feminine plural from an unused root (apparently mean to pierce); holes; Birzoth, an Israelite -- Birzavith (from the marg.).
Perhaps from the root of (H1269) Birzowth; iron (as cutting); by extension, an iron implement -- (ax) head, iron. see HEBREW (H1269) Birzowth
From (H1270) barzel; iron-hearted; Barzillai, the name of three Israelites -- Barzillai. see HEBREW (H1270) barzel

column8: chase away; drive away, fain, flee away, put to flight, make haste, reach, run away, shoot
column9: A primitive root; to bolt, i.e. Figuratively, to flee suddenly -- chase (away); drive away, fain, flee (away), put to flight, make haste, reach, run away, shoot.
By transposition for (H978) Bacharuwmiy; a Barchumite, or native of Bachurim -- Barhumite. see HEBREW (H978) Bacharuwmiy
From (H1262) barah; fat -- fat. see HEBREW (H1262) barah
Probably by contraction from (H882) b'eriy; Beri, an Israelite -- Beri. see HEBREW (H882) b'eriy
Of uncertain derivation; (only in the plural and with the article) the Berites, a place in Palestine -- Berites.

column8: fat fleshed fed, firm, plenteous, rank
column9: From (H1254) bara' (in the sense of (H1262) barah); fatted or plump -- fat ((fleshed), -ter), fed, firm, plenteous, rank. see HEBREW (H1254) bara' see HEBREW (H1262) barah
Feminine from (H1254) bara'; a creation, i.e. A novelty -- new thing. see HEBREW (H1254) bara'
Feminine from (H1262) barah; food -- meat. see HEBREW (H1262) barah
From (H1272) barach; a bolt -- bar, fugitive. see HEBREW (H1272) barach
Or (shortened) bariach {baw-ree'-akh}; from (H1272) barach; a fugitive, i.e. The serpent (as fleeing), and the constellation by that name -- crooked, noble, piercing. see HEBREW (H1272) barach
The same as (H1281) bariyach; Bariach, an Israelite -- Bariah. see HEBREW (H1281) bariyach
Apparently from the feminine of (H7451) ra' with a prepositional prefix; in trouble; Beriah, the name of four Israelites -- Beriah. see HEBREW (H7451) ra'
Patronymically from (H1283) Briy'ah; a Beriite (collectively) or descendants of Beriah -- Beerites. see HEBREW (H1283) Briy'ah

From (H1262) barah (in the sense of cutting (like (H1254) bara')); a compact (because made by passing between pieces of flesh) -- confederacy, (con-)feder(-ate), covenant, league. see HEBREW (H1262) barah see HEBREW (H1254) bara'
The same as (H1285) briyth; Berith, a Shechemitish deity -- Berith. see HEBREW (H1285) briyth
Feminine of (H1253) bor; vegetable alkali -- sope. see HEBREW (H1253) bor

column8: abundantly, altogether, at all, blaspheme, bless, congratulate, curse, greatly,
column9: A primitive root; to kneel; by implication to bless God (as an act of adoration), and (vice-versa) man (as a benefit); also (by euphemism) to curse (God or the king, as treason) -- X abundantly, X altogether, X at all, blaspheme, bless, congratulate, curse, X greatly, X indeed, kneel (down), praise, salute, X still, thank.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1288) barak -- bless, kneel. see HEBREW (H1288) barak
From (H1288) barak; a knee -- knee. see HEBREW (H1288) barak
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1290) berek -- knee. see HEBREW (H1290) berek

column7: El does bless, the father of one of Job\'s friends
column9: From (H1288) barak and (H410) 'el, God has blessed; Barakel, the father of one of Job's friends -- Barachel. see HEBREW (H1288) barak see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H1288) barak; benediction; by implication prosperity -- blessing, liberal, pool, present. see HEBREW (H1288) barak

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine person
column7: an Israelite, also a valley in Judah
column9: The same as (H1293) Brakah; Berakah, the name of an Israelite, and also of a valley in Palestine -- Berachah. see HEBREW (H1293) Brakah
From (H1288) barak; a reservoir (at which camels kneel as a resting-place) -- (fish-)pool. see HEBREW (H1288) barak

column7: Yah blesses, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Berekyahuw {beh-rek-yaw'-hoo}; from (H1290) berek and (H3050) Yahh; knee (i.e. Blessing) of Jah; Berekjah, the name of six Israelites -- Berachiah, Berechiah. see HEBREW (H1290) berek see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
(Aramaic) perhaps from (H7313) ruwm with a prepositional prefix; properly, highly, i.e. Surely; but used adversatively, however -- but, nevertheless, yet. see HEBREW (H7313) ruwm
Of uncertain derivation; Bera, a Sodomitish king -- Bera.
A primitive root; to lighten (lightning) -- cast forth.
From (H1299) baraq; lightning; by analogy, a gleam; concretely, a flashing sword -- bright, glitter(-ing sword), lightning. see HEBREW (H1299) baraq

column7: flash of lightning, an Israelite leader
column9: The same as (H1300) baraq; Barak, an Israelite -- Barak. see HEBREW (H1300) baraq
Of uncertain derivation; Barkos, one of the Nethimim -- Barkos.
From (H1300) baraq; a thorn (perhaps as burning brightly) -- brier. see HEBREW (H1300) baraq
Or barkath {baw-rek-ath'}; from (H1300) baraq; a gem (as flashing), perhaps the emerald -- carbuncle. see HEBREW (H1300) baraq

column8: make bright, choice, chosen, cleanse be clean, clearly, polished, purify, purge out
column9: A primitive root; to clarify (i.e. Brighten), examine, select -- make bright, choice, chosen, cleanse (be clean), clearly, polished, (shew self) pure(-ify), purge (out).
Probably from (H7562) resha' with a prepositional prefix; with wickedness; Birsha, a king of Gomorrah -- Birsha. see HEBREW (H7562) resha'
Patrial from (H1268) Berowthah; a Berothite, or inhabitant of Berothai -- Berothite. see HEBREW (H1268) Berowthah
From (H1319) basar; cheerful; Besor, a stream of Palestine -- Besor. see HEBREW (H1319) basar
Or (shortened) bsorah {bes-o-raw'}; feminine from (H1319) basar; glad tidings; by implication, reward for good news -- reward for tidings. see HEBREW (H1319) basar

column8: bake, boil, bring forth, roast, seethe, sod be sodden
column9: A primitive root; properly, to boil up; hence, to be done in cooking; figuratively to ripen -- bake, boil, bring forth, roast, seethe, sod (be sodden).
From (H1310) bashal; boiled -- X at all, sodden. see HEBREW (H1310) bashal
Of foreign derivation; Bishlam, a Pers. -- Bishlam.
From an unused root meaning to be fragrant; (compare (H5561) cam) the balsam plant -- spice. see HEBREW (H5561) cam
Or bosem {bo'-sem}; from the same as (H1313) basam; fragrance; by implication, spicery; also the balsam plant -- smell, spice, sweet (odour). see HEBREW (H1313) basam

column7: perfume, a wife of Esau (or perhaps two wives with the same name), also a daughter of Solomon
column9: Feminine of (H1314) besem (the second form); fragrance; Bosmath, the name of a wife of Esau, and of a daughter of Solomon -- Bashemath, Basmath. see HEBREW (H1314) besem

column7: smooth, a region East of the Jordan
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Bashan (often with the article), a region East of the Jordan -- Bashan.
Feminine from (H954) buwsh; shamefulness -- shame. see HEBREW (H954) buwsh
A primitive root; to trample down -- tread.

column8: messenger, preach, publish, show forth, bear, bring, carry, preach
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be fresh, i.e. Full (rosy, (figuratively) cheerful); to announce (glad news) -- messenger, preach, publish, shew forth, (bear, bring, carry, preach, good, tell good) tidings.

column8: body, fat, lean fleshed, kin, mankind, nakedness, self, skin
column9: From (H1319) basar; flesh (from its freshness); by extension, body, person; also (by euphem.) The pudenda of a man -- body, (fat, lean) flesh(-ed), kin, (man-)kind, + nakedness, self, skin. see HEBREW (H1319) basar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1320) basar -- flesh. see HEBREW (H1320) basar

column8: ashamed, confusion, greatly, put to shameful thing
column9: From (H954) buwsh; shame (the feeling and the condition, as well as its cause); by implication (specifically) an idol -- ashamed, confusion, + greatly, (put to) shame(-ful thing). see HEBREW (H954) buwsh

column4: noun feminine; feminine; proper name, feminine
column8: apple of the eye, branch, company, daughter, first, old, owl, town,
column9: From (H1129) banah (as feminine of (H1121) ben); a daughter (used in the same wide sense as other terms of relationship, literally and figuratively) -- apple (of the eye), branch, company, daughter, X first, X old, + owl, town, village. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H1121) ben
Probably from the same as (H1327) battah; a bath or Hebrew measure (as a means of division) of liquids -- bath. see HEBREW (H1327) battah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1324) bath -- bath. see HEBREW (H1324) bath
Probably an orthographical variation for (H1327) battah; desolation -- waste. see HEBREW (H1327) battah
Feminine from an unused root (meaning to break in pieces); desolation -- desolate.

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column7: perhaps "man of God", a nephew of Abraham
column9: Apparently from the same as (H1326) bathah and (H410) 'el; destroyed of God; Bethuel, the name of a nephew of Abraham, and of a place in Palestine -- Bethuel. Compare (H1329) Bthuwl. see HEBREW (H1326) bathah see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H1329) Bthuwl
For (H1328) Bthuw'el; Bethul (i.e. Bethuel), a place in Palestine -- Bethuel. see HEBREW (H1328) Bthuw'el
Feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to separate; a virgin (from her privacy); sometimes (by continuation) a bride; also (figuratively) a city or state -- maid, virgin.
Masculine plural of the same as (H1330) bthuwlah; (collectively and abstractly) virginity; by implication and concretely, the tokens of it -- X maid, virginity. see HEBREW (H1330) bthuwlah

column7: daughter (i.e. worshiper) of Yah, an Eg. woman
column9: From (H1323) bath and (H3050) Yahh; daughter (i.e. Worshipper) of Jah; Bithjah, an Egyptian woman -- Bithiah. see HEBREW (H1323) bath see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to cut, cut off, cut down
column9: A primitive root; to cut in pieces -- thrust through.
A primitive root, to chop up -- divide.
From (H1334) bathar; a section -- part, piece. see HEBREW (H1334) bathar

column7: cutting, a place of unc. location in Isr
column9: The same as (H1335) bether; Bether, a (craggy) place in Palestine -- Bether. see HEBREW (H1335) bether

column7: daughter of multitudes, a name for Heshbon or its gate
column9: From (H1323) bath and a masculine plural from (H7227) rab; the daughter (i.e. City) of Rabbah -- Bath-rabbim. see HEBREW (H1323) bath see HEBREW (H7227) rab
From (H1334) bathar; (with the article) the craggy spot; Bithron, a place East of the Jordan -- Bithron. see HEBREW (H1334) bathar

column7: perhaps "daughter of oath", the mother of Solomon
column9: From (H1323) bath and (H7651) sheba' (in the sense of (H7650) shaba'); daughter of an oath; Bath-Sheba, the mother of Solomon -- Bath- sheba. see HEBREW (H1323) bath see HEBREW (H7651) sheba' see HEBREW (H7650) shaba'

column7: perhaps "daughter of opulence", an Israelite woman, also a Canaanite woman
column9: From (H1323) bath and (H7771) showa'; daughter of wealth; Bath-shua, the same as (H1339) Bath-Sheba' -- Bath-shua. see HEBREW (H1323) bath see HEBREW (H7771) showa' see HEBREW (H1339) Bath-Sheba'
For (H1343) ge'eh; haughty -- proud. see HEBREW (H1343) ge'eh

column8: gloriously, grow up, increase, be risen, triumph
column9: A primitive root; to mount up; hence, in general, to rise, (figuratively) be majestic -- gloriously, grow up, increase, be risen, triumph.
From (H1342) ga'ah; lofty; figuratively, arrogant -- proud. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah
Feminine from (H1342) ga'ah; arrogance -- pride. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah

column7: majesty of El, a Gadite spy
column9: From (H1342) ga'ah and (H410) 'el; majesty of God; Geuel, an Israelite -- Geuel. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column8: excellency, haughtiness, highness, pride, proudly, swelling
column9: From (H1342) ga'ah; arrogance or majesty; by implication, (concretely) ornament -- excellency, haughtiness, highness, pride, proudly, swelling. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah
From (H1342) ga'ah; the same as (H1346) ga'avah -- arrogancy, excellency(-lent), majesty, pomp, pride, proud, swelling. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah see HEBREW (H1346) ga'avah

column8: excellent things, lifting up, majesty, pride, proudly, raging
column9: From (H1342) ga'ah; the same as (H1346) ga'avah -- excellent things, lifting up, majesty, pride, proudly, raging. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah see HEBREW (H1346) ga'avah
From (H1342) ga'ah: haughty -- proud. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah

column8: in any wise, at all, avenger, deliver, next kinsfolk, purchase,
column9: A primitive root, to redeem (according to the Oriental law of kinship), i.e. To be the next of kin (and as such to buy back a relative's property, marry his widow, etc.) -- X in any wise, X at all, avenger, deliver, (do, perform the part of near, next) kinsfolk(-man), purchase, ransom, redeem(-er), revenger.
A primitive root, (rather identified with (H1350) ga'al, through the idea of freeing, i.e. Repudiating); to soil or (figuratively) desecrate -- defile, pollute, stain. see HEBREW (H1350) ga'al
From (H1351) ga'al; profanation -- defile. see HEBREW (H1351) ga'al
Feminine passive participle of (H1350) ga'al; redemption (including the right and the object); by implication, relationship -- kindred, redeem, redemption, right. see HEBREW (H1350) ga'al

column8: the top or rim, a boss, a vault
column9: From an unused root meaning to hollow or curve; the back (as rounded (compare (H1460) gev and (H1479) guwph); by analogy, the top or rim, a boss, a vault, arch of eye, bulwarks, etc. -- back, body, boss, eminent (higher) place, (eye)brows, nave, ring. see HEBREW (H1460) gev see HEBREW (H1479) guwph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1354) gab -- back. see HEBREW (H1354) gab
From (H1461) guwb; a log (as cut out); also well or cistern (as dug) -- beam, ditch, pit. see HEBREW (H1461) guwb
Probably from (H1461) guwb (compare (H1462) gowb); a locust (from its cutting) -- locust. see HEBREW (H1461) guwb see HEBREW (H1462) gowb
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H1461) guwb; a pit (for wild animals) (as cut out) -- den. see HEBREW (H1461) guwb
Or (fully) Gowb {gobe'}; from (H1461) guwb; pit; Gob, a place in Palestine -- Gob. see HEBREW (H1461) guwb
From an unused root meaning probably to collect; a reservoir; by analogy, a marsh -- marish, pit.

column8: exalt, be haughty, be make higher, lift up, mount up, be proud, raise up great height, upward
column9: A primitive root; to soar, i.e. Be lofty; figuratively, to be haughty -- exalt, be haughty, be (make) high(-er), lift up, mount up, be proud, raise up great height, upward.
From (H1361) gabahh; lofty (literally or figuratively) -- high, proud. see HEBREW (H1361) gabahh

column8: excellency, haughty, height, high, loftiness, pride
column9: From (H1361) gabahh; elation, grandeur, arrogance -- excellency, haughty, height, high, loftiness, pride. see HEBREW (H1361) gabahh

column8: haughty, height, higher, lofty, proud, exceeding proudly
column9: Or (fully) gabowahh {gaw-bo'-ah}; from (H1361) gabahh; elevated (or elated), powerful, arrogant -- haughty, height, high(-er), lofty, proud, X exceeding proudly. see HEBREW (H1361) gabahh
From (H1361) gabahh; pride -- loftiness, lofty. see HEBREW (H1361) gabahh

column8: border, bound, coast, great, landmark, limit, quarter, space
column9: Or (shortened) gbul {gheb-ool'}; from (H1379) gabal; properly, a cord (as twisted), i.e. (by implication) a boundary; by extens. The territory inclosed -- border, bound, coast, X great, landmark, limit, quarter, space. see HEBREW (H1379) gabal
Or (shortened) gbulah {gheb-oo-law'}; feminine of (H1366) gbuwl; a boundary, region -- border, bound, coast, landmark. Place. see HEBREW (H1366) gbuwl

column8: champion, chief, excel, giant, man, mighty man, one, strong man,
column9: Or (shortened) gibbor {ghib-bore'}; intensive from the same as (H1397) geber; powerful; by implication, warrior, tyrant -- champion, chief, X excel, giant, man, mighty (man, one), strong (man), valiant man. see HEBREW (H1397) geber

column8: force, mastery, might, mighty act, power, power, strength
column9: Feminine passive participle from the same as (H1368) gibbowr; force (literally or figuratively); by implication, valor, victory -- force, mastery, might, mighty (act, power), power, strength. see HEBREW (H1368) gibbowr
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1369) gbuwrah; power -- might. see HEBREW (H1369) gbuwrah
From an unused root meaning to be high (in the forehead); bald in the forehead -- forehead bald.
From the same as (H1371) gibbeach; baldness in the forehead; by analogy, a bare spot on the right side of cloth -- bald forehead, X without. see HEBREW (H1371) gibbeach
From the same as (H1354) gab; collective -- Gabbai, an Israelite -- Gabbai. see HEBREW (H1354) gab

column7: trenches, a place North of Jer
column9: Plural of (H1356) geb; cisterns; Gebim, a place in Palestine -- Gebim. see HEBREW (H1356) geb
From an unused root (meaning to be convex); a goblet; by analogy, the calyx of a flower -- house, cup, pot.
From (H1396) gabar; a master -- lord. see HEBREW (H1396) gabar
Feminine of (H1376) gbiyr; a mistress -- queen. see HEBREW (H1376) gbiyr
From an unused root (probably meaning to freeze); crystal (from its resemblance to ice) -- pearl.
A primitive root; properly, to twist as a rope; only (as a denominative from (H1366) gbuwl) to bound (as by a line) -- be border, set (bounds about). see HEBREW (H1366) gbuwl
From (H1379) gabal (in the sense of a chain of hills); a mountain; Gebal, a place in Phoenicia -- Gebal. see HEBREW (H1379) gabal

column7: a region South of the Dead Sea
column9: The same as (H1380) Gbal; Gebal, a region in Idumaea -- Gebal. see HEBREW (H1380) Gbal
: patrial from (H1380) Gbal; a Gebalite, or inhabitant of Gebal -- Giblites, stone-squarer. see HEBREW (H1380) Gbal
From (H1379) gabal; a twisted chain or lace -- end. see HEBREW (H1379) gabal
From an unused root meaning to be arched or contracted; hunch-backed -- crookbackt.
Feminine from the same as (H1384) gibben; curdled milk -- cheese. see HEBREW (H1384) gibben
From the same as (H1384) gibben; a hump or peak of hills -- high. see HEBREW (H1384) gibben
From the same as (H1375) gbiya', a hillock; Geba, a place in Palestine -- Gaba, Geba, Gibeah. see HEBREW (H1375) gbiya'
By permutation for (H1389) gib'ah; a hill; Giba, a place in Palestine -- Gibeah. see HEBREW (H1389) gib'ah
Feminine from the same as (H1387) Geba'; a hillock -- hill, little hill. see HEBREW (H1387) Geba'
The same as (H1389) gib'ah; Gibah; the name of three places in Palestine -- Gibeah, the hill. see HEBREW (H1389) gib'ah
From the same as (H1387) Geba'; hilly; Gibon, a place in Palestine -- Gibeon. see HEBREW (H1387) Geba'
Prolonged from (H1375) gbiya'; the calyx of a flower -- bolled. see HEBREW (H1375) gbiya'
Patrial from (H1391) Gib'own; a Gibonite, or inhabitant of Gibon -- Gibeonite. see HEBREW (H1391) Gib'own
From the same as (H1375) gbiya'; hilliness; Gibath -- Gibeath. see HEBREW (H1375) gbiya'
Patrial from (H1390) Gib'ah; a Gibathite, or inhabitant of Gibath -- Gibeathite. see HEBREW (H1390) Gib'ah

column8: exceed, confirm, be great, be mighty, prevail, put to more strength, strengthen, be stronger,
column9: A primitive root; to be strong; by implication, to prevail, act insolently -- exceed, confirm, be great, be mighty, prevail, put to more (strength), strengthen, be stronger, be valiant.
From (H1396) gabar; properly, a valiant man or warrior; generally, a person simply -- every one, man, X mighty. see HEBREW (H1396) gabar
The same as (H1397) geber; Geber, the name of two Israelites -- Geber. see HEBREW (H1397) geber
From (H1396) gabar; the same as (H1397) geber; a person -- man. see HEBREW (H1396) gabar see HEBREW (H1397) geber
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1399) gbar -- certain, man. see HEBREW (H1399) gbar
(Aramaic) intensive of (H1400) gbar; valiant, or warrior -- mighty. see HEBREW (H1400) gbar
Intensive of (H1399) gbar; Gibbar, an Israelite -- Gibbar. see HEBREW (H1399) gbar
From (H1397) geber and (H410) 'el; man of God; Gabriel, an archangel -- Garbriel. see HEBREW (H1397) geber see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Feminine of (H1376) gbiyr; mistress -- lady, mistress. see HEBREW (H1376) gbiyr
Intensive from (H1389) gib'ah; a hilly spot; Gibbethon, a place in Palestine -- Gibbethon. see HEBREW (H1389) gib'ah

column8: roof of the house, house top of the house
column9: Probably by reduplication from (H1342) ga'ah; a roof; by analogy, the top of an altar -- roof (of the house), (house) top (of the house). see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah
From (H1413) gadad (in the sense of cutting); coriander seed (from its furrows) -- coriander. see HEBREW (H1413) gadad
A variation of (H1409) gad; Fortune, a Babylonian deity -- that troop. see HEBREW (H1409) gad
From (H1464) guwd (in the sense of distributing); fortune -- troop. see HEBREW (H1464) guwd

column7: a son of Jacob, also his tribe and its territory, also a prophet
column9: From (H1464) guwd; Gad, a son of Jacob, including his tribe and its territory; also a prophet -- Gad. see HEBREW (H1464) guwd
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1489) gizbar; a treasurer -- treasurer. see HEBREW (H1489) gizbar
By reduplication from (H1413) gadad (in the sense of cutting) cleft; Gudgodah, a place in the Desert -- Gudgodah. see HEBREW (H1413) gadad

column8: assemble selves by troops, gather selves together, self in troops, cut selves
column9: A primitive root (compare (H1464) guwd); to crowd; also to gash (as if by pressing into) -- assemble (selves by troops), gather (selves together, self in troops), cut selves. see HEBREW (H1464) guwd
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1413) gadad; to cut down -- hew down. see HEBREW (H1413) gadad
From an unused root (meaning to cut off); a border of a river (as cut into by the stream) -- bank.

column8: army, band of men, company, troop of robbers
column9: From (H1413) gadad; a crowd (especially of soldiers) -- army, band (of men), company, troop (of robbers). see HEBREW (H1413) gadad
Or (feminine) gdudah {ghed-oo-daw'}; from (H1413) gadad; a furrow (as cut) -- furrow. see HEBREW (H1413) gadad
Feminine participle passive of (H1413) gadad; an incision -- cutting. see HEBREW (H1413) gadad

column8: aloud, elder, exceedingly, far, man of great man, matter, thing, high,
column9: Or (shortened) gadol {gaw-dole'}; from (H1431) gadal; great (in any sense); hence, older; also insolent -- + aloud, elder(-est), + exceeding(-ly), + far, (man of) great (man, matter, thing,-er,-ness), high, long, loud, mighty, more, much, noble, proud thing, X sore, (X) very. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal

Or (shortened) gdullah {ghed-ool-law'}; or (less accurately) gduwllah {ghed-ool-law'}; feminine of (H1419) gadowl; greatness; (concretely) mighty acts -- dignity, great things(-ness), majesty. see HEBREW (H1419) gadowl
Or (shortened) gidduph {ghid-doof'}; and (feminine) gidduphah {ghid-doo-faw'}; or gidduphah {ghid-doo-faw'}; from (H1422) gduwphah; vilification -- reproach, reviling. see HEBREW (H1422) gduwphah
Feminine passive participle of (H1442) gadaph; a revilement -- taunt. see HEBREW (H1442) gadaph
From the same as (H1415) gadah; a young goat (from browsing) -- kid. see HEBREW (H1415) gadah
From (H1409) gad; fortunate; Gadi, an Israelite -- Gadi. see HEBREW (H1409) gad
Patronymically from (H1410) Gad; a Gadite (collectively) or descendants of Gad -- Gadites, children of Gad. see HEBREW (H1410) Gad
Intensive for (H1424) Gadiy; Gaddi, an Israelite -- Gaddi. see HEBREW (H1424) Gadiy

column7: El is my fortune, an Israelite
column9: From (H1409) gad and (H410) 'el; fortune of God; Gaddiel, an Israelite -- Gaddiel. see HEBREW (H1409) gad see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or gadyah {gad-yaw'}; the same as (H1415) gadah; a river brink -- bank. see HEBREW (H1415) gadah
Feminine of (H1423) gdiy; a young female goat -- kid. see HEBREW (H1423) gdiy
From an unused root (meaning to heap up); a stack of sheaves; by analogy, a tomb -- shock (stack) (of corn), tomb.

column8: advance, boast, bring up, exceed, excellent, become, do, give,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to twist (compare (H1434) gdil), i.e. To be (causatively make) large (in various senses, as in body, mind, estate or honor, also in pride) -- advance, boast, bring up, exceed, excellent, be(-come, do, give, make, wax), great(-er, come to...estate, + things), grow(up),increase, lift up, magnify(-ifical), be much set by, nourish (up), pass, promote, proudly (spoken), tower. see HEBREW (H1434) gdil
From (H1431) gadal; large (literally or figuratively) -- great, grew. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal
From (H1431) gadal; magnitude (literally or figuratively) -- greatness, stout(-ness). see HEBREW (H1431) gadal
From (H1431) gadal (in the sense of twisting); thread, i.e. A tassel or festoon -- fringe, wreath. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal

column7: very great, one of the Nethinim, also one of Solomon\'s servants
column9: From (H1431) gadal; stout; Giddel, the name of one of the Nethinim, also of one of \"Solomon's servants\" -- Giddel. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal

Or (prolonged) Gdalyahuw {ghed-al-yaw'- hoo}; from (H1431) gadal and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has become great; Gedaljah, the name of five Israelites -- Gedaliah. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H1431) gadal; I have made great; Giddalti, an Israelite -- Giddalti. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal

column7: to hew, hew down or off
column8: cut asunder, in sunder, down, off, hew down
column9: A primitive root; to fell a tree; generally, to destroy anything -- cut (asunder, in sunder, down, off), hew down.
From (H1438) gada'; feller (i.e. Warrior); Gidon, an Israelite -- Gideon. see HEBREW (H1438) gada'
From (H1438) gada'; a cutting (i.e. Desolation); Gidom, a place in Palestine -- Gidom. see HEBREW (H1438) gada'
From (H1438) gada'; warlike (compare (H1439) Gid'own); Gidoni, an Israelite -- Gideoni. see HEBREW (H1438) gada' see HEBREW (H1439) Gid'own
A primitive root; to hack (with words), i.e. Revile -- blaspheme, reproach.

column7: to wall up or off, to build a wall
column8: close up, fence up, hedge, enclose, make up a wall, mason, repairer
column9: A primitive root; to wall in or around -- close up, fence up, hedge, inclose, make up (a wall), mason, repairer.
From (H1443) gadar; a circumvallation -- wall. see HEBREW (H1443) gadar
: the same as (H1444) geder; Geder, a place in Palestine -- Geder. see HEBREW (H1444) geder

column4: proper name; proper name, of a location; proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: wall, three cities in Isr., also a Benjamite
column9: Or (fully) Gdowr {ghed-ore'}; from (H1443) gadar; inclosure; Gedor, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites -- Gedor. see HEBREW (H1443) gadar
From (H1443) gadar; a circumvallation; by implication, an inclosure -- fence, hedge, wall. see HEBREW (H1443) gadar
Feminine of (H1447) gader; enclosure (especially for flocks) -- (sheep-) cote (fold) hedge, wall. see HEBREW (H1447) gader
The same as (H1448) gderah; (with the article) Gederah, a place in Palestine -- Gederah, hedges. see HEBREW (H1448) gderah
Plural of (H1448) gderah; walls; Gederoth, a place in Palestine -- Gederoth. see HEBREW (H1448) gderah
Patrial from (H1445) Geder; a Gederite, or inhabitant of Geder -- Gederite. see HEBREW (H1445) Geder
Patrial from (H1449) Gderah; a Gederathite, or inhabitant of Gederah -- Gederathite. see HEBREW (H1449) Gderah

column7: double wall, a place in Judah
column9: Dual of (H1448) gderah; double wall; Gederothajim, a place in Palestine -- Gederothaim. see HEBREW (H1448) gderah
Probably a clerical error for (H2088) zeh; this -- this. see HEBREW (H2088) zeh

column7: to depart, be cured or healed
column9: A primitive root; to remove (a bandage from a wound, i.e. Heal it) -- cure.
From (H1455) gahah; a cure -- medicine. see HEBREW (H1455) gahah
A primitive root; to prostrate oneself -- cast self down, stretch self.
Another form for (H1460) gev; the back -- back. see HEBREW (H1460) gev
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1460) gev; the middle -- midst, same, there- (where-) in. see HEBREW (H1460) gev
From (H1342) ga'ah (corresponding to (H1354) gab); the back; by analogy, the middle -- + among, back, body. see HEBREW (H1342) ga'ah see HEBREW (H1354) gab
A primitive root; to dig -- husbandman.
From (H1461) guwb; the locust (from its grubbing as a larvae) -- grasshopper, X great. see HEBREW (H1461) guwb

column7: the name of an Israelite, also leader of a northern nation
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Gog, the name of an Israelite, also of some nothern nation -- Gog.
A primitive root (akin to (H1413) gadad); to crowd upon, i.e. Attack -- invade, overcome. see HEBREW (H1413) gadad
Feminine of (H1460) gev; the back, i.e. (by extensive) the person -- body. see HEBREW (H1460) gev
The same as (H1465) gevah; exaltation; (figuratively) arrogance -- lifting up, pride. see HEBREW (H1465) gevah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1466) gevah -- pride. see HEBREW (H1466) gevah
A primitive root (compare (H1494) gazaz); properly, to shear off; but used only in the (figuratively) sense of passing rapidly -- bring, cut off. see HEBREW (H1494) gazaz
Or (shortened) gozal {go-zawl'}; from (H1497) gazal; a nestling (as being comparatively nude of feathers) -- young (pigeon). see HEBREW (H1497) gazal

column7: a city and area in Mesopotamia
column9: Probably from (H1468) guwz; a quarry (as a place of cutting stones); Gozan, a province of Assyria -- Gozan. see HEBREW (H1468) guwz

column4: noun masculine; proper name, of a people
column9: Rarely (shortened) goy {go'-ee}; apparently from the same root as (H1465) gevah (in the sense of massing); a foreign nation; hence, a Gentile; also (figuratively) a troop of animals, or a flight of locusts -- Gentile, heathen, nation, people. see HEBREW (H1465) gevah
Prolonged for (H1465) gevah; a body, whether alive or dead -- (dead) body, carcase, corpse. see HEBREW (H1465) gevah
Or (shortened) golah {go-law'}; active participle feminine of (H1540) galah; exile; concretely and collectively exiles -- (carried away), captive(-ity), removing. see HEBREW (H1540) galah

column7: a city and a region East of the Jordan in Manasseh
column9: From (H1473) gowlah; captive; Golan, a place east of the Jordan -- Golan. see HEBREW (H1473) gowlah
Of uncertain derivation; a pit -- pit.
Probably from (H1598) ganan; protected; Guni, the name of two Israelites -- Guni. see HEBREW (H1598) ganan
Patronymically from (H1476) Guwniy; a Gunite (collectively with article prefix) or descendants of Guni -- Gunites. see HEBREW (H1476) Guwniy

column8: die, be dead, give up the ghost, perish
column9: A primitive root; to breathe out, i.e. (by implication) expire -- die, be dead, give up the ghost, perish.
A primitive root; properly, to hollow or arch, i.e. (figuratively) close; to shut -- shut.
From (H1479) guwph; a corpse (as closed to sense) -- body. see HEBREW (H1479) guwph

column8: abide, assemble, be afraid, dwell, fear, gather together, inhabitant, remain,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to turn aside from the road (for a lodging or any other purpose), i.e. Sojourn (as a guest); also to shrink, fear (as in a strange place); also to gather for hostility (as afraid) -- abide, assemble, be afraid, dwell, fear, gather (together), inhabitant, remain, sojourn, stand in awe, (be) stranger, X surely.
Or (shortened) gur {goor}; perhaps from (H1481) guwr; a cub (as still abiding in the lair), especially of the lion -- whelp, young one. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr

column7: sojourning, dwelling, a place in Palestine
column9: The same as (H1482) guwr; Gur, a place in Palestine -- Gur. see HEBREW (H1482) guwr
Or (feminine) gorah {go-raw'}; a variation of (H1482) guwr -- whelp. see HEBREW (H1482) guwr

column7: dwelling of Baal, a place in Arabia
column9: From (H1481) guwr and (H1168) Ba'al; dwelling of Baal; Gur- Baal, a place in Arabia -- Gur-baal. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al

Or (shortened) goral {go-ral'}; from an unused root meaning to be rough (as stone); properly, a pebble, i.e. A lot (small stones being used for that purpose); figuratively, a portion or destiny (as if determined by lot) -- lot.
Or rather (by permutation) giysh {gheesh}; of uncertain derivation; a mass of earth -- clod.
From (H1494) gazaz; a fleece (as shorn); also mown grass -- fleece, mowing, mown grass. see HEBREW (H1494) gazaz
Of foreign derivation; treasurer -- treasurer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1489) gizbar -- treasurer. see HEBREW (H1489) gizbar
A primitive root (akin to (H1468) guwz); to cut off, i.e. Portion out -- take. see HEBREW (H1468) guwz
Feminine from (H1494) gazaz; a fleece -- fleece. see HEBREW (H1494) gazaz
Patrial from the unused name of a place apparently in Palestine; a Gizonite or inhabitant of Gizoh -- Gizonite.

A primitive root (akin to (H1468) guwz); to cut off; specifically to shear a flock or shave the hair; figuratively to destroy an enemy -- cut off (down), poll, shave, ((sheep-)) shear(-er). see HEBREW (H1468) guwz
From (H1494) gazaz; shearer; Gazez, the name of two Israelites -- Gazez. see HEBREW (H1494) gazaz
From (H1491) gazah; something cut, i.e. Dressed stone -- hewed, hewn stone, wrought. see HEBREW (H1491) gazah

column8: catch, consume, exercise robbery, pluck off, rob, spoil, take away by force, violence,
column9: A primitive root; to pluck off; specifically to flay, strip or rob -- catch, consume, exercise (robbery), pluck (off), rob, spoil, take away (by force, violence), tear.

column8: robbery, thing taken away by violence
column9: From (H1497) gazal; robbery, or (concretely) plunder -- robbery, thing taken away by violence. see HEBREW (H1497) gazal
From (H1497) gazal; plunder, i.e. Violence -- violence, violent perverting.. Gozal. See (H1469) gowzal. see HEBREW (H1497) gazal see HEBREW (H1469) gowzal
Feminine of (H1498) gazel and mean the same: see HEBREW (H1498) gazel
From an unused root meaning to devour; a kind of locust -- palmer-worm.
From the same as (H1501) gazam; devourer -- Gazzam, one of the Nethinim -- Gazzam. see HEBREW (H1501) gazam
From an unused root meaning to cut down (trees); the trunk or stump of a tree (as felled or as planted) -- stem, stock.

column8: cut down off, decree, divide, snatch
column9: A primitive root; to cut down or off; (figuratively) to destroy, divide, exclude, or decide -- cut down (off), decree, divide, snatch.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1504) gazar; to quarry; determine -- cut out, soothsayer. see HEBREW (H1504) gazar
From (H1504) gazar; something cut off; a portion -- part, piece. see HEBREW (H1504) gazar

column7: portion, a Levitical city on the border of Ephraim
column9: The same as (H1506) gezer; Gezer, a place in Palestine -- Gazer, Gezer. see HEBREW (H1506) gezer
Feminine of (H1506) gezer; the figure or person (as if cut out); also an inclosure (as separated) -- polishing, separate place. see HEBREW (H1506) gezer
From (H1504) gazar; a desert (as separated) -- not inhabited. see HEBREW (H1504) gazar
(Aramaic) from (H1505) gzar (as (H1504) gazar); a decree -- decree. see HEBREW (H1505) gzar see HEBREW (H1504) gazar

(in the m patrial from (H1507) Gezer; a Gezerite (collectively) or inhabitants of Gezer; but better (as in the text) by transposition Girziy {gher-zee'}; patrial of (H1630) Griziym; a Grizite (collectively) or member of a native tribe in Palestine -- Gezrites. see HEBREW (H1507) Gezer see HEBREW (H1630) Griziym
Probably from (H1518) giyach; the external abdomen, belly (as the source of the faetus (compare (H1521) Giychown)) -- belly. see HEBREW (H1518) giyach see HEBREW (H1521) Giychown
Or (feminine) gacheleth {gah-kheh'-leth}; from an unused root meaning to glow or kindle; an ember -- (burning) coal.
From an unused root meaning to burn; flame; Gacham, a son of Nahor -- Gaham.
From an unused root meaning to hide; lurker; Gachar, one of the Nethinim -- Gahar.

Or (shortened) gay {gah'-ee}; probably (by transmutation) from the same root as (H1466) gevah (abbreviated); a gorge (from its lofty sides; hence, narrow, but not a gully or winter-torrent) -- valley. see HEBREW (H1466) gevah
Probably from (H1464) guwd; a thong (as compressing); by analogy, a tendon -- sinew. see HEBREW (H1464) guwd

column8: break forth, labor to bring forth, come forth, draw up, take out
column9: Or (shortened) goach {go'-akh}; a primitive root; to gush forth (as water), generally to issue -- break forth, labor to bring forth, come forth, draw up, take out.
(Aramaic) or (shortened) guwach (Aramaic) {goo'- akh}; corresponding to (H1518) giyach; to rush forth -- strive. see HEBREW (H1518) giyach

column7: perhaps "a spring", a place in Benjamin
column9: From (H1518) giyach; a fountain; Giach, a place in Palestine -- Giah. see HEBREW (H1518) giyach

column7: a bursting forth, one of the rivers of Eden, also a spring near Jer
column9: Or (shortened) Gichown {ghee-khone'}; from (H1518) giyach; stream; Gichon, a river of Paradise; also a valley (or pool) near Jerusalem -- Gihon. see HEBREW (H1518) giyach

column7: perhaps "valley of vision", servant of Elisha
column9: Or Gechaziy {gay-khah-zee'}; apparently from (H1516) gay' and (H2372) chazah; valley of a visionary; Gechazi, the servant of Elisha -- Gehazi. see HEBREW (H1516) gay' see HEBREW (H2372) chazah

column8: be glad, joy, be joyful, rejoice
column9: Or (by permutation) guwl {gool}; a primitive root; properly, to spin round (under the influence of any violent emotion), i.e. Usually rejoice, or (as cringing) fear -- be glad, joy, be joyful, rejoice.

column8: exceedingly, gladness, greatly, joy, rejoicing, sort
column9: From (H1523) giyl; a revolution (of time, i.e. An age); also joy -- X exceedingly, gladness, X greatly, joy, rejoice(-ing), sort. see HEBREW (H1523) giyl
Or giylath {ghee-lath'}; feminine of (H1524) giyl; joy -- joy, rejoicing. see HEBREW (H1524) giyl
Patrial from (H1542) Giloh; a Gilonite or inhabitant of Giloh -- Gilonite. see HEBREW (H1542) Giloh
Of uncertain derivation; Ginath, an Israelite -- Ginath.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1615) gir; lime -- plaster. see HEBREW (H1615) gir
From the same as (H1487) guwsh; lumpish; Geshan, an Israelite -- Geshan. see HEBREW (H1487) guwsh
From (H1556) galal; something rolled, i.e. A heap of stone or dung (plural ruins), by analogy, a spring of water (plural waves) -- billow, heap, spring, wave. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
From (H1556) galal; a cup for oil (as round) -- bowl. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
From an unused root meaning to shave; a barber -- barber.
From (H1530) gal and (H1158) ba'ah; fountain of ebullition; Gilboa, a mountain of Palestine -- Gilboa. see HEBREW (H1530) gal see HEBREW (H1158) ba'ah
By reduplication from (H1556) galal; a wheel; by analogy, a whirlwind; also dust (as whirled) -- heaven, rolling thing, wheel. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1534) galgal; a wheel -- wheel. see HEBREW (H1534) galgal
A variation of (H1534) galgal -- wheel. see HEBREW (H1534) galgal

column7: circle (of stones), the name of several places in Palestine
column9: The same as (H1536) gilgal (with the article as a properly, noun); Gilgal, the name of three places in Palestine -- Gilgal. See also (H1019) Beyth hag-Gllgal. see HEBREW (H1536) gilgal see HEBREW (H1019) Beyth hag-Gllgal
By reduplication from (H1556) galal; a skull (as round); by implication, a head (in enumeration of persons) -- head, every man, poll, skull. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
From an unused root probably meaning to polish; the (human) skin (as smooth) -- skin.

column8: advertise, appear, bring, carry, lead, go captive into captivity, depart,
column9: A primitive root; to denude (especially in a disgraceful sense); by implication, to exile (captives being usually stripped); figuratively, to reveal -- + advertise, appear, bewray, bring, (carry, lead, go) captive (into captivity), depart, disclose, discover, exile, be gone, open, X plainly, publish, remove, reveal, X shamelessly, shew, X surely, tell, uncover.
(Aramaic) or glat (Aramaic) {ghel-aw'}; corresponding to (H1540) galah -- bring over, carry away, reveal. see HEBREW (H1540) galah
Or (fully) Giyloh {ghee-lo'}; from (H1540) galah; open; Giloh, a place in Palestine -- Giloh. see HEBREW (H1540) galah
Feminine from (H1556) galal; a fountain, bowl or globe (all as round) -- bowl, pommel, spring. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
Or (shortened) gillul {ghil-lool'}; from (H1556) galal; properly, a log (as round); by implication, an idol -- idol. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
From (H1563) galam; clothing (as wrapped) -- clothes. see HEBREW (H1563) galam

column8: they that are carried away captives
column9: Feminine from (H1540) galah; captivity; concretely, exiles (collectively) -- (they that are carried away) captives(-ity). see HEBREW (H1540) galah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1546) galuwth -- captivity. see HEBREW (H1546) galuwth

column7: to be bald, shave, shave off
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be bald, i.e. (causatively) to shave; figuratively to lay waste -- poll, shave (off).
Or gilyown {ghil-yone'}; from (H1540) galah; a tablet for writing (as bare); by analogy, a mirror (as a plate) -- glass, roll. see HEBREW (H1540) galah
From (H1556) galal; a valve of a folding door (as turning); also a ring (as round) -- folding, ring. see HEBREW (H1556) galal

column7: a cylinder, rod, circuit, district, also a district in Palestine
column9: Or (prolonged) Galiylah {gaw-lee-law'}; the same as (H1550) galiyl; a circle (with the article); Galil (as a special circuit) in the North of Palestine -- Galilee. see HEBREW (H1550) galiyl

column4: noun feminine; proper name, of a location
column7: a circuit, boundary, territory, also a district in Palestine
column9: Feminine of (H1550) galiyl; a circuit or region -- border, coast, country. see HEBREW (H1550) galiyl
Plural of (H1552) gliylah; circles; Geliloth, a place in Palestine -- Geliloth. see HEBREW (H1552) gliylah
Plural of (H1530) gal; springs; Gallim, a place in Palestine -- Gallim. see HEBREW (H1530) gal
Perhaps from (H1540) galah; exile; Goljath, a Philistine -- Goliath. see HEBREW (H1540) galah

column8: commit, remove, roll away, down, together, run down, seek occasion, trust,
column9: A primitive root; to roll (literally or figuratively) -- commit, remove, roll (away, down, together), run down, seek occasion, trust, wallow.
From (H1556) galal; dung (as in balls) -- dung. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
From (H1556) galal; a circumstance (as rolled around); only used adverbially, on account of -- because of, for (sake). see HEBREW (H1556) galal
From (H1556) galal, in the sense of (H1560) glal; great; Galal, the name of two Israelites -- Galal. see HEBREW (H1556) galal see HEBREW (H1560) glal
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H1556) galal; weight or size (as if rolled) -- great. see HEBREW (H1556) galal
A variation of (H1557) galal; dung (plural balls of dung) -- dung. see HEBREW (H1557) galal
From (H1561) gelel; dungy; Gilalai, an Israelite -- Gilalai. see HEBREW (H1561) gelel

column7: to wrap up, fold, fold together
column9: A primitive root; to fold -- wrap together.
From (H1563) galam; a wrapped (and unformed mass, i.e. As the embryo) -- substance yet being unperfect. see HEBREW (H1563) galam
Probably by prolonged from (H1563) galam; sterile (as wrapped up too hard); figuratively, desolate -- desolate, solitary. see HEBREW (H1563) galam
A primitive root; to be obstinate -- (inter-)meddle (with).

column7: witness-pile, a memorial of stones East of the Jordan River
column9: From (H1530) gal and (H5707) ed; heap of testimony; Galed, a memorial cairn East of the Jordan -- Galeed. see HEBREW (H1530) gal see HEBREW (H5707) ed

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine; proper name, masculine a.
column7: a region in Palestine, also the name of several Israelites
column9: Probably from (H1567) Gal'ed; Gilad, a region East of the Jordan; also the name of three Israelites -- Gilead, Gileadite. see HEBREW (H1567) Gal'ed

column7: a descendant of Gilead, also an inhabitant of Gilead
column9: Patronymically from (H1568) Gil'ad; a Giladite or descendant of Gilad -- Gileadite. see HEBREW (H1568) Gil'ad
A primitive root; probably to caper (as a goat) -- appear.

column8: again, alike, also, so much as soon, both so
column9: By contraction from an unused root meaning to gather; properly, assemblage; used only adverbially also, even, yea, though; often repeated as correl. Both...and -- again, alike, also, (so much) as (soon), both (so)...and, but, either...or, even, for all, (in) likewise (manner), moreover, nay...neither, one, then(-refore), though, what, with, yea.
A primitive root (literally or figuratively) to absorb -- swallow, drink.
From (H1572) gama'; properly, an absorbent, i.e. The bulrush (from its porosity); specifically the papyrus -- (bul-)rush. see HEBREW (H1572) gama'

column7: a short cubit (from elbow to knuckles of clenched fist)
column9: From an unused root apparently meaning to grasp; properly, a span -- cubit.

column7: men of valor, defenders of Tyre
column9: From the same as (H1574) gomed; a warrior (as grasping weapons) -- Gammadims. see HEBREW (H1574) gomed

column8: as hast served, benefit, desert, deserving, recompense, reward
column9: From (H1580) gamal; treatment, i.e. An act (of good or ill); by implication, service or requital -- + as hast served, benefit, desert, deserving, that which he hath given, recompense, reward. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal
Passive participle of (H1580) gamal; rewarded; Gamul, an Israelite -- Gamul. See also (H1014) Beyth Gamuwl. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal see HEBREW (H1014) Beyth Gamuwl
Feminine of (H1576) gmuwl; meaning the same -- deed, recompense, such a reward. see HEBREW (H1576) gmuwl
Of uncertain derivation; Gimzo, a place in Palestine -- Gimzo.

column7: to deal fully or adequately with, deal out to, wean, ripen
column8: bestow on, deal bountifully, do good, recompense, requite, reward, ripen, serve,
column9: A primitive root; to treat a person (well or ill), i.e. Benefit or requite; by implication (of toil), to ripen, i.e. (specifically) to wean -- bestow on, deal bountifully, do (good), recompense, requite, reward, ripen, + serve, mean, yield.
Apparently from (H1580) gamal (in the sense of labor or burden-bearing); a camel -- camel. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal
Probably from (H1581) gamal; camel-driver; Gemalli, an Israelite -- Gemalli. see HEBREW (H1581) gamal
From (H1580) gamal and (H410) 'el; reward of God; Gamliel, an Israelite -- Gamaliel. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: to end, come to an end, complete
column8: cease, come to an end, fail, perfect, perform
column9: A primitive root; to end (in the sense of completion or failure) -- cease, come to an end, fail, perfect, perform.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1584) gamar -- perfect. see HEBREW (H1584) gamar

column7: a son of Japheth, also his desc., also the wife of Hosea
column9: From (H1584) gamar; completion; Gomer, the name of a son of Japheth and of his descendants; also of a Hebrewess -- Gomer. see HEBREW (H1584) gamar
Or Gmaryahuw {ghem-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from (H1584) gamar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has perfected; Gemarjah, the name of two Israelites -- Gemariah. see HEBREW (H1584) gamar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column4: noun masculine; feminine; proper name, of a location
column9: From (H1598) ganan; a garden (as fenced) -- garden. see HEBREW (H1598) ganan

column8: carry away, indeed, secretly bring, steal away, get by stealth
column9: A primitive root; to thieve (literally or figuratively); by implication, to deceive -- carry away, X indeed, secretly bring, steal (away), get by stealth.
From (H1589) ganab; a stealer -- thief. see HEBREW (H1589) ganab
From (H1589) ganab; stealing, i.e. (concretely) something stolen -- theft. see HEBREW (H1589) ganab
From (H1589) ganab; theft; Genubath, an Edomitish prince -- Genubath. see HEBREW (H1589) ganab
Feminine of (H1588) gan; a garden -- garden. see HEBREW (H1588) gan
Another form for (H1593) gannah -- garden. see HEBREW (H1593) gannah
From an unused root meaning to store; treasure; by implication, a coffer -- chest, treasury.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1595) genez; treasure -- treasure. see HEBREW (H1595) genez
Prolonged from (H1595) genez; a treasury -- treasury. see HEBREW (H1595) genez
A primitive root; to hedge about, i.e. (generally) protect -- defend.
Or Ginnthow {ghin-neth-o'}; from (H1598) ganan; gardener; Ginnethon or Ginnetho, an Israelite -- Ginnetho, Ginnethon. see HEBREW (H1598) ganan
A primitive root; to bellow (as cattle) -- low.
Feminine active participle of (H1600) ga'ah; lowing; Goah, a place near Jerusalem -- Goath. see HEBREW (H1600) ga'ah

column8: abhor, fail, loathe, vilely cast away
column9: A primitive root; to detest; by implication, to reject -- abhor, fail, lothe, vilely cast away.
From (H1602) ga'al; loathing; Gaal, an Israelite -- Gaal. see HEBREW (H1602) ga'al
From (H1602) ga'al; abhorrence -- loathing. see HEBREW (H1602) ga'al
A primitive root; to chide -- corrupt, rebuke, reprove.
From (H1605) ga'ar; a chiding -- rebuke(-ing), reproof. see HEBREW (H1605) ga'ar
A primitive root to agitate violently -- move, shake, toss, trouble.
From (H1607) ga'ash; a quaking; Gaash, a hill in Palestine -- Gaash. see HEBREW (H1607) ga'ash
Of uncertain derivation; Gatam, an Edomite -- Gatam.
From an unused root meaning to arch; the back; by extensive the body or self -- + highest places, himself.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1610) gaph; a wing -- wing. see HEBREW (H1610) gaph
From an unused root meaning to bend; a vine (as twining), especially the grape -- vine, tree.

column7: gopher (a kind of tree or wood)
column9: From an unused root, probably meaning to house in; a kind of tree or wood (as used for building), apparently the cypress -- gopher.
Probably feminine of (H1613) gopher; properly, cypress- resin; by analogy, sulphur (as equally inflammable) -- brimstone. see HEBREW (H1613) gopher
Perhaps from (H3564) kuwr; lime (from being burned in a kiln) -- chalk(-stone). see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
Or (fully) geyr (gare); from (H1481) guwr; properly, a guest; by implication, a foreigner -- alien, sojourner, stranger. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr

column7: the name of several Israelites, also a Benjamite family
column9: Perhaps from (H1626) gerah; a grain; Gera, the name of six Israelites -- Gera. see HEBREW (H1626) gerah
From an unused root meaning to scratch; scurf (from itching) -- scab, scurvy.

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column7: one of David\'s heroes, also a hill near Jer
column9: From the same as (H1618) garab; scabby; Gareb, the name of an Israelite, also of a hill near Jerusalem -- Gareb. see HEBREW (H1618) garab
By reduplication from (H1641) garar; a berry (as if a pellet of rumination) -- berry. see HEBREW (H1641) garar
Feminine plural from (H1641) garar; the throat (as used in rumination) -- neck. see HEBREW (H1641) garar
Patrial from an unused name (of uncertain derivation); a Girgashite, one of the native tribes of Canaan -- Girgashite, Girgasite.
A primitive root; to abrade -- scrape.

column7: to stir up (strife), engage in strife
column9: A primitive root; properly, to grate, i.e. (figuratively) to anger -- contend, meddle, stir up, strive.
From (H1641) garar; the cud (as scraping the throat) -- cud. see HEBREW (H1641) garar

From (H1641) garar (as in (H1625) gerah); properly, (like (H1620) gargar) a kernel (round as if scraped), i.e. A gerah or small weight (and coin) -- gerah. see HEBREW (H1641) garar see HEBREW (H1625) gerah see HEBREW (H1620) gargar

Or (shortened) garon {gaw-rone'}; from (H1641) garar; the throat (compare (H1621) gargrowth) (as roughened by swallowing) -- X aloud, mouth, neck, throat. see HEBREW (H1641) garar see HEBREW (H1621) gargrowth

column7: lodging place, a place near Bethlehem
column9: From (H1481) guwr; a (temporary) residence -- habitation. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr
A primitive root; to cut off -- cut off.
Plural of an unused noun from (H1629) garaz (compare (H1511) Gizriy), cut up (i.e. Rocky); Gerizim, a mountain of Palestine -- Gerizim. see HEBREW (H1629) garaz see HEBREW (H1511) Gizriy
From (H1629) garaz; an axe -- ax. see HEBREW (H1629) garaz
From the same as (H1486) gowral; harsh -- man of great (as in the margin which reads (H1419) gadowl). see HEBREW (H1486) gowral see HEBREW (H1419) gadowl

A primitive root; to be spare or skeleton-like; used only as a denominative from (H1634) gerem; (causative) to bone, i.e. Denude (by extensive, craunch) the bones -- gnaw the bones, break. see HEBREW (H1634) gerem
From (H1633) garam; a bone (as the skeleton of the body); hence, self, i.e. (figuratively) very -- bone, strong, top. see HEBREW (H1633) garam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1634) gerem; a bone -- bone. see HEBREW (H1634) gerem

column7: bony, a name applied to Keilah
column9: From (H1634) gerem; bony, i.e. Strong -- Garmite. see HEBREW (H1634) gerem
From an unused root meaning to smooth; a threshing- floor (as made even); by analogy, any open area -- (barn, corn, threshing-)floor, (threshing-, void) place.
A primitive root; to crush; also (intransitively and figuratively) to dissolve -- break.

column8: abate, clip, diminish, do take away, keep back, restrain, make small, withdraw
column9: A primitive root; to scrape off; by implication, to shave, remove, lessen, withhold -- abate, clip, (di-)minish, do (take) away, keep back, restrain, make small, withdraw.
A primitive root; to bear off violently -- sweep away.
A primitive root; to drag off roughly; by implication, to bring up the cud (i.e. Ruminate); by analogy, to saw -- catch, chew, X continuing, destroy, saw.
Probably from (H1641) garar; a rolling country; Gerar, a Philistine city -- Gerar. see HEBREW (H1641) garar
From an unused root meaning to husk; a kernel (collectively), i.e. Grain -- beaten corn.

column8: cast up out, divorced woman, drive away forth, out, expel, trouble, thrust out
column9: A primitive root; to drive out from a possession; especially to expatriate or divorce -- cast up (out), divorced (woman), drive away (forth, out), expel, X surely put away, trouble, thrust out.

column7: a thing thrust, a thing put forth
